<div1 type="letter">

<opener>
<note>(COPY)</note>

<dateline>Lincoln, Neb., <date>July 25th, 1900</date>.</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Mr. T. E. Calvert,</addrLine>
<addrLine>G. S., Lincoln.</addrLine>
</address>
<salute>Dear Sir: </salute>
</opener>

<p>The following is my estimate of cost of line Toluca to Cody:</p>

<table>
<row><cell>Grading,</cell><cell>$820,153.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Bridging,</cell><cell>203,830.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Superstructure,</cell><cell>741,590.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Ballasting,</cell><cell>212,250.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Fence,</cell><cell>46,200.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Telegraph,</cell><cell>26,300.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Right-of-way,</cell><cell>10,000.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Building,</cell><cell>67,950.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Total, 131.5 miles,</cell><cell>$2,128,273.00</cell></row>
<row><cell>Cost per mile,</cell><cell>$16,200.00</cell></row>
</table>

<p>I have used the unit prices we are doing the work for now on sections opened, and have put a reasonable unit price on the balance.</p>

<p>I have used $25.00 per ton for steel and 51¢ per tie.  This makes cost per mile 66# steel $5,000.  56# $4,500.</p>

<p>The $250.000.00 now appropriated will grade;</p>
<list>
<item>20 miles out of Toluca now under contract.</item>
<item>7 “ at Agency.  Indian work.</item>
<item>14 “ from Corbett East.  Mormon work.</item>
</list>
<p>It may go further if we do not encounter too much classified material.</p>

<p>The distance Toluca to Cody - - - - - - - 131.5 miles.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Yours truly,</salute>
<salute>(Sgd.) I. S. P. Weeks.</salute>
</closer>



</div1>
</body>

